<section class="alert-panel">
    <h2>How to Explain The App</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>I built a small Blazor/.NET project called TARDIS Telemetry Console.</li>
        <li>It is themed after Doctor Who, but the structure is based on an industrial IoT dashboard.</li>
        <li>It uses C# models, Razor components, dependency injection, routing, and a mock telemetry service.</li>
        <li>Each TARDIS subsystem acts like a connected machine or device.</li>
        <li>The service generates simulated readings.</li>
        <li>The app checks those readings against warning and critical thresholds.</li>
        <li>The UI displays system status, sensor values, and active alerts.</li>
        <li>The Simulate Telemetry button mimics new sensor data coming in.</li>
        <li>The View Diagnostics page shows more detail for each subsystem.</li>
        <li>If I continued the project, I would add SQLite for saved settings and alert history.</li>
        <li>After that, I would replace the mock data with MQTT, OPC UA, REST API, database, or middleware-driven telemetry.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

